nodes.text: simple: science has no materialistic origin of anything: dna, rna, brains, eyes, kidneys, potassium, sodium, any of the billions of compounds, time, space, matter, consciosness -- nothing.
And special creation has no nonmaterial cause for anything either. Come to think of it special creation can only rely on nonmaterial causes.
If you think about it, only materialistic mechanisms could be proven (by scientific method, of course) -- prior miracles, on the other hand, certainly cannot be.
You mean like Eclipses. Oh wait. That was a miracle explained by Science!
The Bible. God did not write the Bible, he inspired the people to write it. You are right, no logical contradiction exists.
And that is different how? I told johnny to write that I'm infallible. Therefore the book that I told johnny to write proves I'm infallible. There is no difference.
